# ============================================================================
# CONFIDENTIAL / REAL DATA — NEVER COMMIT  (see docs/SECURITY.md, docs/00 §8)
# Real source/import data and exports stay local. Tests use synthetic fixtures.
# Drop confidential inputs in /data/ (gitignored) — not in the repo root.
# ============================================================================
/data/
/private/
/reports/
*.local
# Common confidential data file types kept out by default (allow-list a synthetic
# fixture explicitly with a negation if one must be committed, e.g. tests/fixtures/*).
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.csv
*.sqlite
*.db
*.dump
*.bak
!tests/**/fixtures/**
# Screenshot of the owner's real BudgetHome.xlsx (creditors/amounts/income) — a UX-spec
# reference kept local-only; see docs/ux/assets/README.md
docs/ux/assets/2026-07-06-payperiod-sheet-reference.png
# Personal data exclusion in Budget Extraction processor
budget-extraction/bank-statements
budget-extraction/budgeteer_import.json
budget-extraction/EXTRACTION_REPORT.md
budget-extraction/EXTRACTION_ROADMAP.md
# SPIKE-11 statement-profiling artifacts (parsed real rows/balances) — local audit trail
budget-extraction/statement-spike/
# #20 statement-import outputs (real amounts/merchants) — committed tooling emits these locally
budget-extraction/statement_import.json
budget-extraction/STATEMENT_EXTRACTION_REPORT.md
budget-extraction/merchant_rules.json


